1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,740


2
00:00:00,740 --> 00:00:03,470
INSTRUCTOR: To conclude,
let's summarize

3
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:06,110
what we have covered today.

4
00:00:06,110 --> 00:00:09,530
In part one, we
introduced a new framework

5
00:00:09,530 --> 00:00:13,370
to identify patients who
do not need treatment

6
00:00:13,370 --> 00:00:20,120
using interpretable AI applied
to transformed real-world data.

7
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:22,670
This helped us
reduce overtreatment

8
00:00:22,670 --> 00:00:26,510
in settings where treatment
efficacy is already

9
00:00:26,510 --> 00:00:28,700
well established.

10
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:32,119
In part two, we went further.

11
00:00:32,119 --> 00:00:35,840
We introduced a framework
to identify patients

12
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:39,110
who truly benefit
from treatment, even

13
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:42,890
when unobserved
confounding is present.

14
00:00:42,890 --> 00:00:46,250
This was achieved by
integrating real-world data

15
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:50,540
with external RCT
benchmarks and applying

16
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:57,230
interpretable AI to safely
extrapolate subgroup effects.

17
00:00:57,230 --> 00:01:03,550
In part three, we turned to
RCT data directly and asked,

18
00:01:03,550 --> 00:01:09,190
can interpretable AI outperform
conventional subgroup analysis?

19
00:01:09,190 --> 00:01:12,520
We showed that it
can by identifying

20
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:18,490
more accurate, data-driven, and
clinically meaningful subgroups.

21
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:21,580
But something is still missing.

22
00:01:21,580 --> 00:01:25,720
The framework we introduced
in part two, or row two,

23
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:28,720
does not apply in all cases.

24
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:34,900
It depends on having a relevant
RCT to guide weight tuning.

25
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:38,470
So what happens when
there is no such RCT,

26
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:42,670
or when the RCT exists, but
the trial population is too

27
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:44,890
different to be informative?

28
00:01:44,890 --> 00:01:48,640
That's where row three comes in.

29
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:51,010
In the next lecture,
we will show you

30
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:54,640
how to identify
treatment benefit using

31
00:01:54,640 --> 00:02:00,190
real-world data alone, even
when no randomized trial exists.

32
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:01,270
Thank you.

33
00:02:01,270 --> 00:02:05,220
And I look forward to continuing
this journey with you.